the event organizers were super energetic and welcoming.
I thought the small group setup was really clever. It's way easier to actually talk and connect, made it feel more intimate and not a speech to a crowd, per say. An hour flew by so fast because the conversations felt natural and never awkward.

It was refreshing to meet people from so many different walks of life, it felt like a crash course in perspectives as much as in English.

Maybe after the small group talks, leave a few minutes for open mingling, itâ€™d be nice to casually chat with the other groups too, I felt really comfortable in my group with kak Ekky, kak Niko and kak Putri, but also a bit disconnected from everyone else. Totally understand the time crunch though! just a quick suggestion if that resonates with you guys :)
